By: Sri Ramakrishna
---
There is a sâdhu in Hrishikesh who gets up early in the morning and
stands near a great waterfall. He looks at it the whole day and says
to God： ‘Ah. You have done well! Well done! How amazing!’ He doesn't
practise any other form of japa or austerity. At night he returns to
his hut.
